        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 13 at 3:56PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 356 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Colonias, or 15 miles northwest of Santa Rosa, moving northeast at
35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colonias.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
